    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-16T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="653"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/1–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-16T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 16, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Your telegram 20, January 6, 2 p.m. In instruction no. 19 of July 15, 1944 to
                    our member on War Crimes Commission, London,<note n="79" xml:id="d653fn1"
                        >Herbert C. Pell; for instruction, see <ref target="frus1944v01#pg_1333">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 1333</ref>.</note> Department took
                    position that for Commission purposes war in Far East started July 7, 1937.
                    Matter is being called to attention of our deputy member on London
                        Commission<note n="80" xml:id="d653fn2">Lt. Col. Joseph V. Hodgson.</note>
                    who will be in London shortly and who will endeavor to expedite decision by
                    Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
